messages.message: Uploaded patch set 1.
Patch Set 1: Sanity-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

Strictly speaking it also depends on all the other QML files in the module, and everything in all imported modules. But maybe we shouldn't go there for now.
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

Can we check if "--only-bytecode" has been passed to qmlcachegen? In that case, we should be able to skip the dependency.

Patch Set 1:

(1 comment)

> Can we check if "--only-bytecode" has been passed to qmlcachegen? In that case, we should be able to skip the dependency.

I don't think that is a good idea. The CMake code is too complex already. There are obvious flaws that will lead to build failures. We need to cut down on the amount of "weird" code paths, not add to them. The condition you outline would only be triggered by someone manually turning the qmldir generation off, while using the new CMake API that was just released and has never supported such stuff. They will quickly learn to either also turn qmlcachegen off or have the qmldir file generated.

messages.message: Uploaded patch set 1.

Patch Set 1: Sanity-Review-1

(1 comment)

See http://wiki.qt.io/Early_Warning_System for explanations.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Let's not work around issues, at least not without a bug filed against the respective component that can be tracked in Jira.

Patch Set 1:

Fix is here https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtdeclarative/+/386548

Patch Set 1:

Qml import scan is now called for widget examples, as far as I can see it is not called in 6.2 and I don't think it should be called. It might happen because WebEngineWidgets is linked against QuickWidgets and QuickPrivate and pulls in QML dependency. I don't know if the webengine project files or the new cmake deploy support is wrong.

This is not a fix just a workaround for a potential cmake issue.

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Qml import scan is now called for widget examples, as far as I can see it is not called in 6.2 and I don't think it should be called. It might happen because WebEngineWidgets is linked against QuickWidgets and QuickPrivate and pulls in QML dependency. I don't know if the webengine project files or the new cmake deploy support is wrong.
> 
> This is not a fix just a workaround for a potential cmake issue.

Sure, and I think in general, a workaround is fine. However, the underlying issue has to be tracked, because I don't expect webengine to be the only one encountering it. Hopefully, Jörg and Alexandru can chime in with a real solution; otherwise, if the issue is unclear, we need a bugreport. And this commit should reference it, so that we can later easily find and revert it once the issue is fixed – otherwise we end up with weird leftovers in our public examples.

And this commit should reference it, so that we can later easily find and revert it once the issue is fixed – otherwise we end up with weird leftovers in our public examples.
